---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout title="Friends of Bright Futures School">
  <div class="prose-bfs">
    <p>
      The Friends of Bright Futures School (FBFS) is a parent and staff association that works to support the educational and social experience of our pupils.
    </p>

    <h2>Our Aims</h2>
    <p>
      The aim of the Association is to advance the education of pupils in the school, in particular by:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Developing effective relationships between the staff, parents and others associated with the school.</li>
      <li>Engaging in activities which support the school and advance the education of the pupils.</li>
      <li>Providing and assisting in the provision of facilities for education at the school, not normally provided by the Local Authority.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Membership</h2>
    <p>
      Membership of FBFS is open to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Parents, guardians or carers of any pupil currently attending the school, and</li>
      <li>Teaching and non-teaching staff.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      FBFS is a charity. Our registration number is <strong>1153766</strong>. We have our own bank account and our main purpose is to raise funds to augment the social and educational experience of pupils.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Become a Friend</h2>
    <p>
      If you would like to become a member of Friends of Bright Futures School, please email us at <a href="mailto:office@brightfuturesschool.co.uk">office@brightfuturesschool.co.uk</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
